==English ==
===Etymology===
Variant of [[Amalia]] or [[Emilia]]. Derived from [[Germanic]] ''[[amal]]'' (work).

===Pronunciation===
a-MEE-lee-a or a-MEEL-ya

===Proper noun===
'''Amelia'''
# a [[female]] [[given name]]

===Namesakes===
Amelia Earhart, the first woman to make a solo flight over the [[Atlantic Ocean]].

